.TH FINDREPOS 1 "September 2024" "findrepos %VERSION%" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
findrepos \- recursively search for bare Git repositories

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B findrepos
[\fIstart-point\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B findrepos
is a utility that recursively searches through directories starting from a given point and identifies directories that are bare Git repositories. A bare Git repository is identified by the presence of a \fBHEAD\fR file directly in the directory.

If no \fIstart-point\fR is provided, the search will start from the current directory.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I start-point
The directory from which to begin the search. If omitted, the program will start from the current directory (`.`).

.SH USAGE
.PP
To search from the current directory:

.nf
    findrepos
.fi

To search from a specific directory:

.nf
    findrepos /path/to/directory
.fi

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start searching for bare Git repositories from the current directory:

.nf
    findrepos
.fi

Start searching for bare Git repositories from the specified directory `/home/user/projects`:

.nf
    findrepos /home/user/projects
.fi

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid arguments (too many arguments or unrecognized option).

.SH SEE ALSO
git(1)

